Class AsyncAgent<E extends Environment>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.irit.smac.amak.Agent<AsyncAmas<E>,E>
      • fr.irit.smac.amak.AsyncAgent<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The environment the agent is connected to.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Schedulable, java.lang.Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AsyncAntExample

    public class AsyncAgent<E extends Environment>
extends Agent<AsyncAmas<E>,E>
implements Schedulable
    This class can be used to create a fully asynchronous agent. This agent must not be connected to any MAS.

    perles
